    Extract model residuals 'nomad_model' class

    residuals.Rd

    This function takes a nomad_model object and extracts model residuals from the underlying mobility::mobility().

    residuals(object, type, ...)

    Arguments

    object

    a nomad_model() object containing the fitted mobility

    type

    the type of residuals to be returned. Available residual types include: 'deviance' (default), 'pearson', and 'raw'.

    ...

    further arguments passed to or from other methods

    Value

    a matrix containing model residuals

    Details

    Residual types are calculated as:

    raw

    \(y_i - \mu_i\)

    pearson

    \((y_i - \mu_i)/\sqrt{\mu_i}\)

    deviance

    \(sign(y_i - \mu_i) * \sqrt(2(log(y_i/\mu_i) - (y_i - \mu_i)))\)

    Where, \(y_i\) is the observed data and \(\mu_i\) is the value predicted by the model using the mean of parameter posterior distributions

    See also

    Other model: check(), compare(), fit_jags(), fit_prob_travel(), mobility(), predict(), summary()

    Author

    John Giles

    Examples

    # Get nomad_model object
nmd_model <- nomad::model_db$zmb_cdr_2020_mod_dd_exp

# Get model residuals
nomad::residuals(nmd_model)
